If "max speed above all" is real: Swift + AppKit + SwiftTerm, single window with a custom tiling view. For your scope (up to 6 terminals, 3×2 default grid), this is maybe a weekend of work and will feel instant in a way nothing else will.

If you want cross-platform without giving up much: Rust + wgpu + alacritty_terminal. You'd be building something in the Wezterm family. More work, but the performance ceiling is nearly identical to native — Alacritty outperforms Terminal.app on macOS despite being cross-platform, because GPU rendering beats AppKit's text rendering for terminal workloads specifically.

