Font rendering is where cross-platform terminals die. macOS users expect SF Mono / Menlo with proper ligatures and emoji fallback. glyphon/cosmic-text handles this reasonably but test early with emoji, CJK, and powerline glyphs. Budget real time for this — it's the #1 place "fast Rust terminal" projects feel janky.

PTY resize signaling. When you resize a tile, you must send TIOCSWINSZ to the PTY and update the Term's grid size. Miss either and you get visual corruption or programs that don't know their new size. alacritty_terminal handles the grid side; portable-pty handles the ioctl.

Input routing. Only the focused tile gets keystrokes. Sounds obvious, but you'll want a clear focus model from day one — click-to-focus plus a keybinding like Cmd+1..6 to jump between tiles. Decide early whether Cmd+W closes a tile or the window.

