The Claude Code angle
The reason this feature is worth its weight: users will create workspaces like "Exploring auth refactor" with three tiles, each a worktree on a different branch, each with its own Claude Code session trying a different approach. At the end, they look at all three, pick the winner, and discard the others. This workflow doesn't really exist in any other tool, and it's what the whole "focused mode" framing is actually for.

Lean into it. Consider a "fork this tile" action: take an existing worktree tile, spawn a new one based on the same branch, so you can try two variations from a common starting point. That's a five-line feature that looks like magic.

