The honest risk list
Things most likely to surprise you:

Font rendering edge cases. Emoji, CJK, powerline glyphs, zero-width joiners. cosmic-text handles these but you'll hit weird cases. Test with a torture file early.
Mouse selection. Multi-line selection with proper wrapping semantics, selection across scrollback boundary, double-click-word and triple-click-line. This consistently takes 2-3x longer than expected in every terminal project.
macOS-specific input quirks. Dead keys, IME for CJK input, Cmd vs. Ctrl semantics. Plan time for this.
Performance under pathological load. yes piped to itself, find /, cat large-log.txt. Easy to get right with the coalescing design we discussed, easy to get wrong if you route every byte through a channel.
wgpu version churn. wgpu still has breaking changes between versions. Pin your version and don't upgrade casually mid-project.
What I'd actually recommend doing next
