Option A: Start writing code. I can sketch focusterm-core with real, compilable types — AppState, Workspace, Tile, Layout, layout rectangle computation with unit tests. You run cargo check and cargo test, we iterate. This is the shortest path from design to running software.

Option B: Nail down the remaining design questions first. Config format, keybinding scheme, theme format, template format. These are small individually but they constrain implementation. Doing them now means less churn later.

I lean toward A — the design questions in B are genuinely small and you'll design them better once you have code to test against. But it depends on how you work. Which do you want to do?

